🟧 2. Clone the Project Repository
Your teammates will use GitHub Desktop for this.

Steps:
Open GitHub Desktop

Click File → Clone Repository

Paste your repo URL

Choose a folder

Click Clone

That’s it.

🟨 3. Open the Project in VS Code
Steps:
Open VS Code

Click File → Open Folder

Select the project folder

Click Open

VS Code will load the entire project.

🟩 4. Install Dependencies
Your project will have two folders:

/backend
/frontend
Each has its own dependencies.

Backend:
Open a terminal in VS Code:

cd backend
npm install
Frontend:

cd frontend
npm install
This installs everything your teammates need.

🟦 5. Run the Project
Backend (Node/Express):

cd backend
npm start
Frontend (React):

cd frontend
npm start
React will open automatically in the browser.

