Configure Express

Configure SQLite

Write SQL

Write backend logic

Write authentication

Write routing

Write middleware

Write database schema

This protects them from complexity and protects your timeline.

🟧 8. Git Workflow (Beginner‑Friendly)
This is the workflow your team will follow.

1. Switch to the dev branch
2. Create a feature branch
Name it like:


feature/inventory-ui
feature/login-page
feature/sales-form
3. Make changes
4. Commit in GitHub Desktop
5. Push the branch
6. Create a Pull Request
7. You review and merge into dev
This keeps the project clean and safe.

🟦 9. Troubleshooting Guide
Beginners panic easily — this section prevents that.

Problem: “npm is not recognized”
Fix: Node.js is not installed correctly. Reinstall Node.

Problem: “npm start doesn’t work”
Fix: Run npm install first.

Problem: “React page is blank”
Fix: Check the browser console for errors.

Problem: “Backend says port in use”
Fix: Close the terminal and restart the backend.

Problem: “I broke Git”
Fix:  
Use GitHub Desktop → Branch → Discard changes  
Or ask you for help.
